<dl><dt class="h2">The Life-Link program</dt>
<dd><ul>
<li class="llspaced">is a Medical Doctor's and some Educators reaction to the Cold War during the 1980s, to a documented despair among teenagers, feeling marginalized and confronted with the risk for Nuclear Weapons annihilation and an Environmental degradation.</li>

<li class="llspaced">The Life-Link program builds on the common sense that we must all, each one of us with urgency consider our/my responsibility for a constructive behaviour towards Myself, towards Others, towards Nature. Life-Link specifies a peace ethics into the three interdependent dimensions of Care for Myself - Care for Others - Care for Nature.</li>

<li class="llspaced">Youth and teachers and parents in classes in more than 600 schools in 80 countries today use the Life-Link program. More than 3 000 performed small care actions ("lessons") have been reported to www.life-link.org Schools&Actions. UNESCO has recognized the Life-Link program, and a pioneering collaboration has started at several UNESCO schools (ASPnet).</li>

<li class="llspaced">The Life-Link program is fully in harmony with United Nations decade Education for Sustainable Development, the Water for Life and Culture of Peace decades included.</li>

<li class="llspaced">The benefits of the concrete Life-Link program can be discussed on six levels: 
Students - Teachers - Schools - Communities - Countries - Planet Earth.</li>
</ul></dd></dl>

